					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The narrator's haughty, conceited tone put me off at first (I read the story in Vincent Price's voice) but I realized that was what you were going for and accepted it. That was at the line &quot;Wouldn't that be just perfect&quot;, which is also when I realized that this was AWCY.</p> <p>There should be more tales like this: worthwhile, to-the-point capsules of story.</p> 
				 	]]>
