				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-560445#post-1557947</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-560445/patronage#post-1557947</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 06 Sep 2012 19:22:42 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>1324229</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I have reservations about taking this into my head cannon, but I really like the idea. At first, I objected, thinking that Evil Sotheby's wouldn't have any use for art, as they mostly seem focused on catering to the fucked-up tastes of the ultra-rich. Then I remembered their goal of procuring</p> <blockquote> <p>rare and obscure items, along with providing its members the most exclusive, expensive, and rare experiences available</p> </blockquote> <p>Transcendent anomalous art? Yep, this fits! +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
